//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
//
// File: zannastudio/src/ui/scene_editor_2d.zia
// Purpose: Visual tileset/tile/layer/object editor for canonical Game2D scene
//          files.
// Key invariants:
//   - Zanna.Game2D.SceneDocument is the only editable scene source of truth.
//   - Every accepted mutation immediately refreshes Document.content as
//     canonical JSON, so normal save/session/recovery paths remain authoritative.
//   - One paint or object-drag gesture creates one gap-free history snapshot.
//   - Compact windows show canvas or inspector at full width, never two slivers.
//   - Raster work is bounded even for malformed or resource-limit-sized maps.
//   - Layer images resolve through bounded preview caches; broken references
//     never invalidate or rewrite authored scene JSON.
//   - Multi-object property, layout, nudge, and selection commands commit once
//     or restore the complete prior selection/content; inspector inputs never
//     own scene keys.
//   - Scene-level typed metadata follows the same canonical, no-op-safe history
//     path as object properties.
//   - Project components add only missing typed object properties across a
//     selection, aborting atomically on every type conflict.
//   - Project schema authoring has independent conflict-safe file history and
//     never changes canonical scene content, revision, history, or dirty state.
//   - Objects use a retained expandable hierarchy with stable multi-selection;
//     direct child creation, parent choices, and row drops reorder complete
//     subtrees through one rollback-safe snapshot.
//   - Canvas point and marquee selection share conventional Shift-add and
//     Control/Command-toggle semantics, remain workspace-only, and always
//     release pointer capture on completion or cancellation.
//   - Paint/erase, rectangle, flood-fill, and tile-pick tools are active-layer
//     scoped; mutations commit once while previews, picks, and canceled
//     captured gestures never enter canonical scene history.
//   - Hierarchy Find keeps all bounded rows visible, wraps deterministically,
//     reveals nested matches, and never changes canonical scene history.
// Ownership/Lifetime:
//   - Main owns one controller; WorkbenchShell owns its persistent host widgets.
//   - The controller borrows the active Document and recreates its model on
//     document/content changes.
// Links: zannastudio/src/core/document.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_clipboard.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_component_authoring_controller.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_component_palette.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_component_schema.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_hierarchy_search.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_layout_2d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_property_inspector_2d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_tileset_2d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_tileset_inspector_2d.zia,
//        docs/zannalib/game/scene.md,
//        docs/adr/0174-scene-object-authoring-metadata-and-duplication.md,
//        docs/adr/0156-listbox-selected-row-data.md,
//        docs/adr/0158-scene-level-property-authoring.md,
//        docs/adr/0160-project-scene-component-schemas.md,
//        docs/adr/0163-stable-multiselect-and-row-aware-treeview-editing.md,
//        docs/adr/0164-backward-compatible-2d-scene-object-hierarchy.md,
//        docs/adr/0165-scrollview-descendant-reveal.md,
//        docs/adr/0170-studio-2d-canvas-marquee-selection.md,
//        docs/adr/0171-bounded-scene-flood-fill-and-studio-tile-tools.md
//
//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

